#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:2
#: 717904533f394bc1a67ecd00eda3542c
msgid "Cylinder Flow (Vortex Shedding)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:4
#: 5a839e730d854e219ab0d669a0262d86
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The transient counterpart to the steady cavity examples. The script "
"``examples/fluid/cylinder_flow/cylinder_flow.py`` runs the classic *flow "
"past a circular cylinder* benchmark — a long rectangular channel with a "
"small cylinder near the inlet. At :math:`\\mathrm{Re} = 100` the wake "
"becomes unstable, vortices shed alternately from the top and bottom of "
"the cylinder, and a **von Kármán vortex street** propagates downstream. "
"The geometry and parameters follow the DFG 2D-1 benchmark (Schäfer & "
"Turek, 1996), which gives reference values for drag/lift coefficients and"
" the Strouhal number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:17
#: a2b8f89932894a259d6043b11a37f84c
msgid "Problem"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:19
#: 9e9117287be840659f00ece8a2a4ebcb
msgid "The transient incompressible Navier-Stokes system,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:21
#: 39dc861c90b348f1aed3929bf1cad0b3
msgid ""
"\\rho\\, \\frac{\\partial \\mathbf{u}}{\\partial t}\n"
"+ \\rho\\, (\\mathbf{u} \\cdot \\nabla)\\mathbf{u}\n"
"\\;=\\; -\\nabla p + \\mu\\, \\Delta \\mathbf{u},\n"
"\\qquad \\nabla \\cdot \\mathbf{u} = 0,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:28
#: 876af0c945764277846754e3c3882737
msgid ""
"on the channel :math:`\\Omega = [0, 2.2] \\times [0, 0.41]` with a "
"circular cylinder of radius :math:`r = 0.05` centered at :math:`(0.2, "
"0.2)`. Boundary conditions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:32
#: ad45e6342ce448e5b3d9e79b451b7b25
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"inlet (:math:`x = 0`): parabolic profile :math:`u_x(y) = "
"4\\,U_\\text{max}\\, y\\, (H - y) / H^2`, :math:`u_y = 0`,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:35
#: bdabe08e13e24e74857e2092e6b51f08
msgid "walls and cylinder surface: no-slip,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:36
#: a7aee585cbd541f8828fbbfb2141c85d
msgid "outlet (:math:`x = 2.2`): \"do-nothing\" + pressure pin,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:38
#: e188d451debe45f1a276c9c7378dda8e
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"with :math:`U_\\text{max} = 1.5` giving :math:`\\bar{U} = 1`, :math:`D = "
"0.1`, :math:`\\rho = 1`, :math:`\\mu = 10^{-3}`, and hence "
":math:`\\mathrm{Re} = \\rho \\bar{U} D / \\mu = 100`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:44
#: ee89033e22da416d973d02757b3e1e64
msgid "Time integration: implicit Euler"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:46
#: b27aaf3d82a44483814e5e49acdccf45
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The transient term :math:`\\rho\\, \\partial_t \\mathbf{u}` is "
"discretized with backward Euler — implicit, unconditionally stable. Each "
"timestep solves"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:50
#: af211f5bc896421893041d3367d7cf9c
msgid ""
"\\rho\\, \\frac{\\mathbf{u}^{n+1} - \\mathbf{u}^{n}}{\\Delta t}\n"
"+ \\rho\\, (\\mathbf{u}^{n} \\cdot \\nabla)\\mathbf{u}^{n+1}\n"
"\\;=\\; -\\nabla p^{n+1} + \\mu\\, \\Delta \\mathbf{u}^{n+1},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:56
#: c256744e06d548d9995ab2ca7852079a
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"(convection linearized by lagging the advecting velocity to "
":math:`\\mathbf{u}^n`). The script implements this as a transient variant"
" of the cavity assembler, with the mass term :math:`\\rho/\\Delta t "
"\\cdot u\\, v` added to the diagonal block along with a corresponding "
"SUPG residual:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:62
#: f2686ee4dcfa49a69bbf90a86c7cdcf8
msgid "examples/fluid/cylinder_flow/cylinder_flow.py (essence)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:80
#: bf38dca00eeb4c47a18538b5f8e68d03
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The previous-timestep solution :math:`\\mathbf{u}^n` enters the RHS "
"through a separate ``NodeAssembler`` (``MomentumRHSAssembler``) that "
"contributes :math:`\\rho/\\Delta t\\, \\mathbf{u}^n \\cdot v`. Both "
"assemblers share the same ``tau`` field, updated each step to reflect the"
" local cell Reynolds number."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:88
#: 14b8960a453445b5a6f389527209b875
msgid "Stabilization"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:90
#: 0ab60bb76f3144ffbcfd0ca0c5dc7905
msgid ""
"The cylinder problem is more demanding than the cavity: upstream cells "
"see nearly-uniform flow, the wake region needs fine-grained convection-"
"dominated stabilization. The script uses an **adaptive** :math:`\\tau`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:95
#: 33650c0497794191a27efa2d6e744818
msgid ""
"\\tau \\;=\\;\n"
"\\left[\n"
"  \\left(\\frac{2}{\\Delta t}\\right)^2\n"
"  + \\left(\\frac{2|\\mathbf{u}|}{h}\\right)^2\n"
"  + \\left(\\frac{4\\nu}{h^2}\\right)^2\n"
"\\right]^{-1/2},"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:104
#: 4cdfe57b07f74d9e8fba857edd773fa7
msgid ""
"evaluated per element from the local mesh size :math:`h` and velocity "
"magnitude. This makes the diffusive part of SUPG dominate where the flow "
"is slow and the convective part dominate in the wake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:111
#: fb93ad15018146909ad3388b525ea6c5
msgid "Post-processing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:113
#: d592a72fec6c4d57a117f0fa914ef5c7
msgid "Two derived fields are computed at every saved frame:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:115
#: 3d59ed12609749478c395e9af812cd5d
msgid ""
"**Vorticity** :math:`\\omega = \\partial_x v - \\partial_y u` — computed "
"by L² projection: assemble a mass matrix "
":class:`~tensormesh.MassElementAssembler`, project :math:`\\partial_x v -"
" \\partial_y u` evaluated on quadrature points back onto the nodal basis,"
" solve :math:`M \\omega = \\tilde\\omega`. Standard postprocessing recipe"
" for piecewise-linear FEM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:122
#: fd34c5b4f36646c19e91141313498c5c
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"**Drag and lift coefficients** on the cylinder surface — the script "
"integrates the surface traction :math:`\\mathbf{t} = (\\sigma \\cdot "
"\\mathbf{n})` over the cylinder facets via a "
":class:`~tensormesh.FacetAssembler` instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:127
#: 4990d06483ef4343841feb36a82e1756
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"For a Strouhal number :math:`\\mathrm{St} = f D / \\bar{U}` of about "
"0.30, the script's plotted lift coefficient should oscillate at roughly "
":math:`f \\approx 3` Hz once the wake stabilizes (typically after "
":math:`t \\gtrsim 5`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:134
#: 909c1af785b24adc96b7f230029679fa
msgid "Output and rendering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:136
#: 7b93ab356b1d457d91f03888a6c917f3
msgid ""
"**Frame sequence.** Every ``N`` steps the script writes a VTU with the "
"velocity, pressure, and vorticity fields. ParaView opens the whole "
"sequence as a time series."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:139
#: 575d129b887d4829be85af42bb4019bb
msgid ""
"**MP4 rendering.** The companion script "
"``examples/fluid/cylinder_flow/render_video.py`` rasterizes the VTU "
"sequence into ``cylinder_flow.mp4`` via PyVista + ffmpeg."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:142
#: 603368faa2704e06affa1556afde168b
msgid ""
"**Final snapshot.** ``cylinder_flow_final.png`` is a three-panel static "
"figure (vorticity, speed, pressure) of the last step, for inclusion in "
"talks and reports."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/example_gallery/fluid/cylinder_flow.rst:154
#: 7f0d2bcc448d42ee82247e8782bb4b31
msgid ""
"*Output of* ``cylinder_flow.py`` *(rendered to MP4 by* "
"``render_video.py``\\ *): the developed von Kármán vortex street behind "
"the cylinder. After an initial symmetric phase, a small asymmetry "
"triggers periodic shedding; vortices alternate sign and convect "
"downstream at roughly the inlet velocity.*"
msgstr ""

